Business Brief -- Cominco Ltd.:
   Firm Drops Out of Group
   Developing Quebec Deposit
The balance of the Louvicourt deposit, which has been
hailed as one of Canada's biggest base-metal discoveries in
recent years, will be owned 30% by Aur Resources Inc., a
Toronto exploration outfit that discovered the deposit, and
45% by Louvem Mines Inc., a 52%-owned subsidiary of Noranda
Inc. of Toronto.
   Officials at Cominco and Teck couldn't be reached to
comment. The companies also hold indirect stakes in
Louvicourt through a combined 21% equity interest in Aur
Resources.